Column Comment.0: SUPPORT FACILITY SUBTYPE: check constraint value that is used to maintain therelationship between SUPPORT FACILITY and its various sub-types. In this table,may only be SF_VESSEL.
Column Comment.1: VESSEL IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the marine vessel.
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: AREA ID: Unique identifier for any named area such as a country, province, projectarea, area of interest, offshore area, district etc.
Column Comment.4: AREA TYPE: Unique identifier for the type of area, such as country, state, AOI etc.
Column Comment.5: BACKUP ANTENNA LOCATION: the location of the backup antenna on the vessel.
Column Comment.6: BACKUP ANTENNA TYPE: The type of location antenna that is used as backup onthe vessel.
Column Comment.7: CURRENT OPERATOR: The business associate who is currently the operator of thevessel.
Column Comment.8: DRILLING HOLE POSITION: The location on a vessel that describes the position ofthe drilling hole through which operations proceed.
Column Comment.9: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.10: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.11: COORDINATE ACQUISITION METHOD: The method used by the vessel forcoordinate acquisition, such as GPS positioning, triangulation etc.
Column Comment.12: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.13: PRIMARY ANTENNA LOCATION: the location on the vessel of the primarynavigation antenna.
Column Comment.14: PRIMARY ANTENNA TYPE: The type of primary antenna used for positioning on thisvessel.
Column Comment.15: REMARK: Narrative remarks relating to this row of data.
Column Comment.16: SECONDARY ANTENNA LOCATION: the location on the vessel of the secondarynavigation antenna.
Column Comment.17: SECONDARY ANTENNA TYPE: the type of navigation antenna used.
Column Comment.18: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.19: VESSEL BEAM: The width of a vessel.
Column Comment.20: VESSEL DISPLACEMENT: The quantity of water displaced by a ship, the weight ofthe displaced liquid being equal to that of the displacing body.
Column Comment.21: VESSEL DRAFT: The depth of water necessary to float a ship, or the depth of watera ship displaces when loaded.
Column Comment.22: VESSEL LENGTH: the overall length of the vessel from stern to bow.
Column Comment.23: VESSEL NAME: the registered name for the vessel.
Column Comment.24: VESSEL SIZE: A valid reference to the size of the vessel. Do not put dimensions ordisplacement in this table. This refers to the class of vessel, such as those foundhere http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Ships_by_type
Column Comment.25: VESSEL TYPE: The type of marine vessel, such as seismic recording, drilling rig,surveying, passenger.
Column Comment.26: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.27: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.28: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.29: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.30: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.31: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.32: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
